A total of 102 health workers in Nasarawa State have tested positive for Coronavirus. Chairman of the Nigeria Medical Association (NMA) in the state, Dr. Peter Umaru, who disclosed this to journalists in Lafia, the state capital, said 77 infected healthcare workers are from the public facilities while 25 are from private facilities. He disclosed that among those infected are himself and president of Association of Resident Doctors (ARD), Dr Peter Idoko. The chairman disclosed further that both himself and the chairman of the ARD have since been discharged having been cured of the virus and tested nagitve of the disease.